300 g Tilapia
113 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Carrot, julienned
1 unit(s) Lime
2 unit(s) Green Onion
4 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
1 unit(s) Peanut Butter
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 tbsp Moo Shu Spice Blend
2 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
3 unit(s) Radish
1 tbsp Oil*
2 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Thinly slice radishes.
Add radish, carrots, vinegar, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water and 2 tsp (4 tsp) sugar to a small pot. Season with salt. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Once simmering, cook, stirring often, until sugar dissolves, 1-2 min.
Transfer radish and carrots, including liquid, to a large bowl. Set aside in the fridge to cool.
Add peanut butter packets and 1 cup warm water (same for 4 ppl) to a small bowl to soften.

Zest, then juice lime.
Core, then thinly slice pepper.
Thinly slice green onions, keeping whites and greens separate.

Remove peanut butter from bowl and discard water.
Add peanut butter, half the hoisin sauce, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lime juice, and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to the same bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Whisk until smooth.

Pat tilapia dry with paper towels. Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then tilapia, Moo Shu Spice Blend and green onion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tilapia turns opaque, 3-5 min**.
Remove from heat. Add lime zest and remaining hoisin sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to mix.

Strain and discard all pickling liquid from radish and carrots. Add peppers, spring mix, cucumbers and peanut-lime dressing to radish and carrots. Toss to coat.
Divide salad between plates.
Top with tilapia.
Sprinkle crispy shallots and remaining green onions over top.

If you've opted to get tilapia, pat tilapia dry with paper towels. Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Cook in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the shrimp, increasing cooking time to 3-5 min**, until tilapia turns opaque. Follow the rest of the recipe as written.